{"by":"deepsun","id":47769809,"kids":[47769850],"parent":47768813,"text":"If Flock collects and processes PII data, then all their customers are &quot;subprocessors&quot;. Flock should really have a Data Processing Agreement with their subprocessors, to legally ensure they follow the same PII handling controls as Flock does.<p>For example, if Flock receives a legitimate request to delete some data, then Flock must forward that request to all their Data Processors (e.g. including AWS&#x2F;GCP&#x2F;Cloudflare) and they must delete it as well.","time":1776193029,"type":"comment"}